text:
Reliable? No. It is not a HubSpot thing.

Since most of the email clients don't support style tags or external resources or they block those, you should use web-safe fonts â€“ at least add them as a fallback.

This is supported by apple, but the mail app will still block external resources automatically. You can add an HTML module with content:
```&lt;link href="<https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Anton&amp;display=swap>" rel="stylesheet"&gt;

{% require_css %}
    &lt;style&gt;      
      @font-face {
    font-family: 'Roboto';
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 400;
    src: url(<https://fonts.gstatic.com/s/anton/v23/1Ptgg87LROyAm3K8-C8CSKlvPfE.woff2>) format('woff2');
    }
      * {
        font-family: 'Anton', sans-serif;
      }
    &lt;/style&gt;


&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;
&lt;style type="text/css"&gt;
* {
font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;![endif]--&gt;

{% end_require_css %}```
And add inline styles for text: `&lt;p style="font-family: 'Anton', sans-serif;"&gt;`
